# API & services conventions

- **All requests go through** `@/core/api` (`apiClient`).
- **Type-safe responses**: `apiClient<MyResponse>(...)` and define `MyResponse` in feature `types/`.
- **Centralized error handling**:
  - Throw/propagate `ApiError` from the API layer.
  - Feature services may map errors to user-friendly messages, but don’t swallow errors silently.
- **No hard-coded base URLs**: use `@/core/config`.
- **Keep services slim**: request/response mapping only; heavy transforms go in `features/<x>/utils`.
